1. MATLAB GUI Based PID Temperature Control System

Developed a MATLAB GUI for analyzing and tuning a PID-based temperature control system. The interface allows modification and comparison of PID parameters (Kp, Ki, Kd) 
while visualizing real-time temperature and PWM responses for performance evaluation. The GUI framework was adapted and further enhanced from an existing open-source implementation.

2. Simulink Based Closed-Loop Temperature Control System

Designed and simulated a closed-loop temperature control system in MATLAB Simulink using PID and PWM techniques. The system continuously compares desired and actual temperature,
regulates heater power through PWM control, and models thermal behavior using transfer functions to achieve stable temperature regulation with minimal overshoot and improved 
settling response.
